{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "banking-app-gateway-9090",
    "name": "Banking App API Gateway",
    "description": "Digital Wallet Backend through API Gateway\n\nBase URL: http://localhost:9090\n\nFeatures: JWT Auth, Tiered Rate Limiting (Redis), Request Validation\n\nHeaders enforced by gateway:\n- Content-Type: application/json\n- Channel: WEBP | SWIFTY | BANKAPP | MOBILEMONEY | SAMONEY\n- AppId: <string>\n- AppVersion: <semver>\n- RequestId: <uuid>\n- Authorization: Bearer <jwt> (protected endpoints only)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Authentication",
      "description": "Public endpoints – no JWT required",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Register New User",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "{{channel}}" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "{{appId}}" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/auth/register", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "auth", "register"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{username}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Register a new user. Creates User + Wallet (balance 0.0). Returns JWT token.\n\n**Validation**:\n- username: @NotBlank, @Size(min=3, max=50)\n- password: @NotBlank, @Size(min=6)"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Capture token and user details for later use",
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"authToken\", json.token);",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"userId\", json.userId);",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"username\", json.username);",
                  "    console.log('Registered user:', json.username, 'ID:', json.userId);",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.log('Registration failed:', json);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Login",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "{{channel}}" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "{{appId}}" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/auth/login", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{username}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Authenticate and receive JWT token.\n\n**Note**: Credentials must match registered user.\n\n**Response**: AuthResponse{token, username, role, userId}"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"authToken\", json.token);",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"userId\", json.userId);",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"role\", json.role);",
                  "    console.log('Logged in as:', json.username);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Wallet Endpoints",
      "description": "Require JWT (Authorization: Bearer <token>)\n\nChannel tier affects rate limits:\n- WEBP: SILVER (100 req/s)\n- SWIFTY/BANKAPP: GOLD (400 req/s)\n- MOBILEMONEY/SAMONEY: BRONZE (20 req/s)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Balance",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "{{channel}}" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "{{appId}}" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/wallet/balance", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "wallet", "balance"] },
            "description": "Get current wallet balance.\n\n**Security**: Authenticated (any role)\n**Response**: WalletDto{id, userId, username, balance}\n\n**Errors**:\n- 401: No/invalid JWT\n- 404: Wallet not found"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    var data = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"walletId\", data.id);",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"balance\", data.balance);",
                  "    console.log('Balance:', data.balance);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Transfer Funds",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "{{channel}}" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "{{appId}}" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/wallet/transfer", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "wallet", "transfer"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"receiverId\": {{receiverId}},\n  \"amount\": {{amount}},\n  \"reference\": \"{{transferRef}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Transfer funds to another user.\n\n**Validation**:\n- amount ≥ 1.0 (minTransferAmount)\n- amount ≤ 100,000 (maxTransferAmount)\n- reference must be unique (idempotency)\n\n**Business Rules**:\n- Sender balance must be sufficient\n- Creates Transaction record (type=TRANSFER)\n- Deducts sender, credits receiver in single @Transactional\n\n**Response**: TransactionDto{id, senderId, receiverId, amount, type, reference, createdAt}\n\n**Errors**:\n- 400: Invalid amount / Insufficient funds\n- 404: Wallet not found\n- 409: Duplicate reference"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"lastTransactionId\", json.id);",
                  "    console.log('Transfer successful:', json.amount, 'to', json.receiverId);",
                  "} else {",
                  "    console.log('Transfer failed:', json);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Request Top-Up",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "{{channel}}" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "{{appId}}" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/wallet/topup/request", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "wallet", "topup", "request"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"amount\": {{topupAmount}}\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Create a top-up request (requires ADMIN approval).\n\n**Validation**:\n- amount > 0\n- amount ≤ 1,000,000 (wallet.topup.max-amount)\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Creates TopUpRequest with status=PENDING\n2. Admin approves → Wallet credited + Transaction created (type=TOP_UP)\n3. Admin rejects → Status set to REJECTED\n\n**Response**: TopUpResponseDto{id, userId, amount, status, createdAt}\n\n**Errors**:\n- 400: Invalid amount"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"topUpRequestId\", json.id);",
                  "    console.log('Top-up requested:', json.amount, 'status:', json.status);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Transaction History",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "{{channel}}" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "{{appId}}" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/wallet/transactions", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "wallet", "transactions"] },
            "description": "Get user's transaction history (sent & received).\n\n**Returns**: List<TransactionDto> ordered by createdAt DESC.\n\n**Transaction Types**:\n- TRANSFER: Money sent/received\n- TOP_UP: Admin credit to wallet\n\n**No parameters required** – identity from JWT token."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    console.log('Transactions count:', json.length);",
                  "    if (json.length > 0) {",
                  "        console.log('Latest transaction:', json[0]);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Admin Endpoints",
      "description": "Require JWT with ROLE_ADMIN.\n\nUse Channel BANKAPP or SWIFTY (GOLD tier preferred for high limits).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Direct Top-Up (Admin)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/admin/topup", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "admin", "topup"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": {{targetUserId}},\n  \"amount\": {{adminTopupAmount}},\n  \"reference\": \"{{adminRef}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "Admin directly credits a user's wallet (no approval needed).\n\n**Validation**:\n- userId must exist\n- amount > 0\n- reference unique (auto-generated if omitted)\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Validates amount limits\n2. Check for duplicate reference (idempotency)\n3. Credits wallet immediately (UPDATE wallets SET balance = balance + ?)\n4. Creates Transaction record (type=TOP_UP)\n\n**Response**: TransactionDto{id, senderId=null, receiverId=userId, amount, type=TOP_UP, reference, createdAt}\n\n**Errors**:\n- 400: Invalid amount / Duplicate reference\n- 404: User wallet not found\n- 403: Non-ADMIN user"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    console.log('Admin top-up completed:', json.amount, 'to user', json.receiverId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Pending Top-Up Requests",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/admin/topup/requests", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "admin", "topup", "requests"] },
            "description": "List all top-up requests with status=PENDING, ordered by createdAt DESC.\n\n**Use Case**: Admin dashboard to review pending requests.\n\n**Response**: List<TopUpResponseDto>{id, userId, amount, status=PENDING, createdAt}\n\n**No query parameters** – returns all pending globally."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    console.log('Pending top-up requests:', json.length);",
                  "    if (json.length > 0) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set(\"pendingRequestId\", json[0].id);",
                  "        console.log('First pending request ID:', json[0].id, 'amount:', json[0].amount);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Approve Top-Up Request",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/admin/topup/requests/{{pendingRequestId}}/approve", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "admin", "topup", "requests", "{{pendingRequestId}}", "approve"] },
            "description": "Approve a pending top-up request.\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Load TopUpRequest by ID (404 if not found)\n2. Validate status is PENDING (400 if already processed)\n3. Call WalletService.adminTopUp(userId, amount, \"TOPUP-\" + requestId)\n4. Update request status → APPROVED\n5. Persist changes @Transactional\n\n**Side Effects**:\n- Wallet balance credited\n- Transaction record created\n\n**Response**: TopUpResponseDto{id, userId, amount, status=APPROVED, createdAt}\n\n**Errors**:\n- 404: Request not found\n- 400: Already processed\n- 403: Non-ADMIN"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    console.log('Approved request:', json.id, 'status:', json.status);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Reject Top-Up Request",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/admin/topup/requests/{{pendingRequestId}}/reject", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "admin", "topup", "requests", "{{pendingRequestId}}", "reject"] },
            "description": "Reject a pending top-up request.\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Load TopUpRequest by ID\n2. Validate status = PENDING\n3. Update status → REJECTED\n4. Save (no wallet changes)\n\n**Response**: TopUpResponseDto with status=REJECTED\n\n**Errors**:\n- 404: Not found\n- 400: Already processed\n- 403: Non-ADMIN"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    console.log('Rejected request:', json.id, 'status:', json.status);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET User Wallet (Admin View)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{adminToken}}" },
              { "key": "Channel", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppId", "value": "BANKAPP" },
              { "key": "AppVersion", "value": "{{appVersion}}" },
              { "key": "RequestId", "value": "{{requestId}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "http://localhost:9090/api/admin/wallet/{{targetUserId}}", "host": ["localhost"], "port": "9090", "path": ["api", "admin", "wallet", "{{targetUserId}}"] },
            "description": "Admin: View any user's wallet balance.\n\n**Path Parameter**: userId\n**Response**: WalletDto{id, userId, username, balance}\n\n**Errors**:\n- 404: Wallet not found\n- 403: Non-ADMIN"
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    console.log('User wallet:', json.username, 'balance:', json.balance);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:9090" },
    { "key": "authToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "adminToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "userId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "username", "value": "test_user_{{timestamp}}" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "SecurePass123!" },
    { "key": "channel", "value": "WEBP" },
    { "key": "appId", "value": "WEBP" },
    { "key": "appVersion", "value": "1.0.0" },
    { "key": "requestId", "value": "{{$guid}}" },
    { "key": "transferRef", "value": "INV-{{timestamp}}" },
    { "key": "adminRef", "value": "ADMIN-{{timestamp}}" },
    { "key": "receiverId", "value": "2" },
    { "key": "amount", "value": "1000" },
    { "key": "topupAmount", "value": "50000" },
    { "key": "adminTopupAmount", "value": "150000" },
    { "key": "targetUserId", "value": "2" },
    { "key": "pendingRequestId", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-generate RequestId if not set",
          "if (!pm.variables.get('requestId') || pm.variables.get('requestId') === '{{$guid}}') {",
          "    pm.variables.set('requestId', pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}'));",
          "}",
          "",
          "// Auto-generate timestamp-based variables",
          "var ts = Date.now();",
          "pm.variables.set('timestamp', ts);",
          "",
          "// Set dynamic username if still default",
          "if (pm.variables.get('username').includes('{{timestamp}}')) {",
          "    pm.variables.set('username', 'user_' + ts);",
          "}",
          "",
          "// Set dynamic references",
          "pm.variables.set('transferRef', 'INV-' + ts);",
          "pm.variables.set('adminRef', 'ADMIN-' + ts);",
          "",
          "// Log for debugging",
          "console.log('Request Headers:', pm.request.headers);",
          "console.log('Using RequestId:', pm.variables.get('requestId'));"
        ],
        "type": "text/javascript"
      }
    }
  ],
  "description": "### Authentication Flow\n\n1. **Register** → Creates user + wallet, returns JWT\n2. **Login** → Validates credentials, returns JWT\n\nSave the `authToken` environment variable.\n\n### Wallet Operations\n\n- **Balance**: GET with JWT\n- **Transfer**: POST with receiverId, amount, reference\n- **Top-Up Request**: POST (requires ADMIN approval)\n- **Transactions**: GET history\n\n### Admin Operations\n\n- **Direct Top-Up**: POST immediate credit\n- **List Pending Requests**: GET all PENDING top-ups\n- **Approve/Reject**: POST by requestId\n- **View User Wallet**: GET by userId\n\n### Rate Limiting\n\nGateway enforces tiered limits per identity (JWT sub / AppId / IP):\n- BRONZE (MOBILEMONEY/SAMONEY): 20 req/s, burst 200\n- SILVER (WEBP): 100 req/s, burst 1000\n- GOLD (SWIFTY/BANKAPP): 400 req/s, burst 5000\n\n### Error Handling\n\nExpected errors:\n- 401: Missing/invalid JWT\n- 403: Insufficient role\n- 400: Validation/amount/insufficient funds\n- 404: Not found\n- 409: Duplicate reference\n- 429: Rate limit exceeded\n\n### Environment Setup\n\nImport this collection into Postman, then create an environment with these variables:\n\n| Variable | Description | Example |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| baseUrl | Gateway URL | http://localhost:9090 |\n| authToken | User JWT token | (from register/login) |\n| adminToken | Admin JWT token | (login as admin) |\n| channel | Request channel | WEBP |\n| appId | App identifier | WEBP |\n| receiverId | Target user for transfer | 2 |\n| targetUserId | User ID for admin ops | 2 |\n\n### Pre-request Script (Auto-set headers)\n\nThe collection event auto-generates `RequestId` and timestamps per request.\n\n### Testing Notes\n\n1. First register a user → captures `authToken` and `userId`\n2. Use that token for wallet endpoints\n3. For admin ops, register/login an admin user first (role=ADMIN)\n4. For transfer `receiverId`, ensure target user exists\n5. Top-up requests require admin approval via separate endpoint\n\n### Database Verification\n\nConnect to PostgreSQL to verify:\n```bash\ndocker exec -it digital-wallet-db psql -U test -d digital_wallet_db\nSELECT * FROM users;\nSELECT * FROM wallets;\nSELECT * FROM transactions ORDER BY created_at DESC;\nSELECT * FROM top_up_requests WHERE status='PENDING';\n```",
  "protocolProfileBehavior": {}
}
